---
import {
    AlertDialog,
    AlertDialogTrigger,
    AlertDialogContent,
    AlertDialogHeader,
    AlertDialogFooter,
    AlertDialogTitle,
    AlertDialogDescription,
    AlertDialogCancel,
} from "@/components/starwind/alert-dialog";
import { Button } from "@/components/starwind/button";
---

<AlertDialog>
    <AlertDialogTrigger asChild>
        <tag id="final-popup-trigger"></tag>
    </AlertDialogTrigger>
    <AlertDialogContent>
        <AlertDialogHeader>
            <AlertDialogTitle class="font-excalifont"
                >A final note</AlertDialogTitle
            >
            <AlertDialogDescription class="text-left">
                Hi it's me, Lakshyajeet Jalal, a final year student of B.Tech
                CSE at GEHU Haldwani. For the past 4 years, I've been
                maintaining this project and I am nearing the end of my journey
                at GEHU.
                <br />
                <br />
                This project started in my fist year, as a young college fresher found
                it difficult to find PYQs for his preparation. What started as a small
                personal project, I started sharing it with my friends. And in no
                time, the url was being shared across various groups and platforms.
                From 5 users to 5000+ in just a single week.
                <br />
                <br />
                Initially this was just a onedrive link. But as the project grew,
                I had to create a website to accommodate the growing userbase and
                content. I started with Jekyll as that was the goto for github pages.
                Then I switched to hugo for while. And then finally I switched to
                Astro, the framework that I fell in love with.
                <br />
                <br />
                Enough technical talk, I just want to say that this project has been
                a huge part of my college life. It has been a great learning experience
                for me and I have had a lot of fun building and maintaining it. I
                am glad that it has been able to help so many students in their preparation.
                <br />
                <br />
                So, as I am nearing the end of my journey at GEHU, I just want to
                say thank you to everyone who has used this project, contributed to
                it, and supported me throughout these years. It has been an amazing
                journey and I am grateful for all the memories and experiences that
                I have had with this project.
                <br />
                <br />
                Give me a follow on my <a
                    href="https://linktr.ee/mglsj"
                    target="_blank"
                    class="text-blue-500 underline">social media handles</a
                > to stay in touch and see what I am up to next or just say hi!
                <br />
                <p class="text-right font-excalifont">- Lakshyajeet Jalal</p>
            </AlertDialogDescription>
        </AlertDialogHeader>
        <AlertDialogFooter>
            <AlertDialogCancel asChild>
                <Button variant="outline" id="final-popup-close">
                    Close
                </Button>
            </AlertDialogCancel>
        </AlertDialogFooter>
    </AlertDialogContent>
</AlertDialog>

<script>
    function triggerFinalPopup() {
        const trigger = document.getElementById("final-popup-trigger");
        if (trigger) {
            trigger.click();
        }

        localStorage.setItem("final-popup-shown", "true");
        localStorage.setItem(
            "final-popup-shown-timestamp",
            Date.now().toString(),
        );
    }
    // Open the dialog when the page loads
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
        const finalPopupShown = localStorage.getItem("final-popup-shown");
        const finalPopupTimestamp = localStorage.getItem(
            "final-popup-shown-timestamp",
        );

        if (finalPopupShown && finalPopupTimestamp) {
            const now = Date.now();
            const timeSinceShown = now - parseInt(finalPopupTimestamp, 10);

            // If the popup was shown more than 1 week, show it again
            if (timeSinceShown > 7 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000) {
                triggerFinalPopup();
            }
        } else if (!finalPopupShown) {
            triggerFinalPopup();
        }
    });
</script>
